The paper discusses the development of an intrusion detection system for in-vehicle networks, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed system uses deep learning models, specifically Generative Adversarial Nets, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The system is designed to detect suspicious network connections, which is related to the subfield of network security (cs.NI). Finally, the paper also discusses the importance of accuracy in the IDS to ensure driver safety, which is related to the subfield of software engineering (cs.SE).
